14mm wide angle lens, ultra-wide field of view with dramatic barrel distortion and exaggerated depth
24mm wide-angle lens, broad field of view with slight perspective distortion at edges
35mm lens, natural field of view with slight wide-angle perspective and environmental context
50mm lens, standard focal length closest to human eye perspective with natural proportions
70mm telephoto lens, compressed background and shallow depth of field isolating the subject
85mm portrait lens, flattering facial proportions with smooth creamy background blur
aerial shot, high overhead perspective looking straight down on the scene
aerial view, elevated vantage point showing the landscape and surroundings from above
angle from above, camera positioned above the subject looking downward
angle from below, camera positioned below the subject looking upward
atmospheric perspective, distant elements appear hazy and faded to create a sense of depth
between fingers, subject framed through a gap between outstretched fingers
between legs, scene viewed through a gap between legs for a dramatic low-angle frame
between thighs, intimate close framing with the viewpoint set between thighs
Big Close-Up (BCU), extremely tight framing capturing the eyes and nose area, face angled with a delicate tilt adding depth and visual interest
birds-eye view, directly overhead perspective looking straight down on the scene
blurry foreground, out-of-focus elements in the near field creating layered depth
body shot, full framing showing the subject from head to toe
Chest Shot (MCU), medium close-up framing from mid-chest to above the head, torso angled slightly with one shoulder closer to the camera for natural pose
cinematic shot, wide aspect ratio with dramatic lighting and cinematic color grading
close-up, tight framing on the subject emphasizing facial features and expression, head slightly tilted or turned with subtle shoulder angle for natural depth
close-up portrait, tightly cropped portrait of the face and upper shoulders, head angled slightly with a natural tilt and one shoulder turned toward the camera
close-up shot, narrow framing highlighting fine details and textures, subject posed with a gentle head turn and relaxed asymmetric posture
cowboy shot, frames the subject from mid-thigh up in classic western film style
crane shot, elevated sweeping camera movement from a high boom position
cut-in, inserted detail shot focusing on a specific object or action
depth of field, controlled focus plane separating the sharp subject from a blurred background
Detail Shot (ECU), extreme close-up isolating a small specific detail like an eye or hand
dolly zoom, simultaneous zoom and camera movement creating a disorienting perspective shift
drone shot, smooth aerial perspective from a low-flying unmanned camera
dutch angle, camera tilted on its axis creating a diagonal horizon line for tension
establishing shot, wide opening view showing the full environment and setting context
extreme close-up shot, very tight frame revealing minute surface details and textures
extreme wide shot, vast wide frame with the subject appearing small within the environment
eye-level shot, camera positioned at the subject's natural eye height for neutral perspective
face close-up, tight frame on the face capturing expression and skin detail, head gently tilted with eyes at a slight angle to the camera
Face Shot (VCU), very close-up centered on the face from forehead to chin, subtle head rotation with a slight three-quarter angle for dimension
first-person view, subjective camera angle showing the scene from the subject's own eyes
fisheye lens, extreme barrel distortion creating a spherical wide-angle effect
focus sharp, all elements rendered with crisp clarity and precise detail
from above, downward-angled viewpoint showing the top of the subject
from above front, high angle looking down from the front
from above front three-quarter, high angle looking down from a front-diagonal position
from above rear, high angle looking down from behind
from above rear three-quarter, high angle looking down from a rear-diagonal position
from above side, high angle looking down from a lateral position
from behind, rear perspective showing the back of the subject
from behind over the shoulder, rear view with the subject glancing back over their shoulder
from below, upward-angled viewpoint looking up at the subject
from below front, low angle looking up from directly in front
from below front three-quarter, low angle looking up from a front-diagonal position
from below rear, low angle looking up from behind
from below rear three-quarter, low angle looking up from a rear-diagonal position
from below side, low angle looking up from a lateral position
from outside, view through a window or doorway looking inward from an exterior position
from side, lateral perspective showing the subject in profile
front three-quarter view, angled approximately forty-five degrees between front and side showing depth and dimension
front view, direct frontal perspective facing the subject head-on
full body shot, complete framing of the subject from head to feet with minimal cropping
full shot, wide enough to include the entire subject and some surrounding environment
gopro view, ultra-wide action camera perspective with barrel distortion and dynamic angle
ground level shot, camera placed flat on the ground for a dramatic low perspective
half face close-up, tight framing showing one half of the face split vertically, head turned to present the featured side with dramatic angle
hatching (texture), rendered with fine parallel crosshatched lines creating tonal shading
high angle shot, camera elevated above the subject angled downward
hip level shot, camera positioned at the subject's hip height looking slightly upward
knee level shot, camera at knee height creating a low-angle upward perspective
long shot, distant framing showing the full subject with extensive surrounding environment
low angle shot, camera positioned low looking upward at the subject for imposing effect
macro lens, extreme close-up magnification revealing fine textures and tiny details
medium close-up shot, frames the subject from approximately chest level up, body turned at a gentle angle with head tilted for engaging composition
medium shot, frames the subject from approximately the waist up
medium wide shot, frames the subject with generous surrounding environment visible
multiple views, showing the subject from several different angles in one composition
over the shoulder shot, framed from behind one subject's shoulder toward another subject
overhead angle, camera positioned directly above looking straight down
panorama, ultra-wide sweeping horizontal view capturing an expansive scene
panoramic landscape, wide horizontal frame spanning a broad natural landscape
perspective, converging lines and diminishing scale creating three-dimensional depth
portrait, vertical framing centered on the subject's face and upper body, shoulders turned at a slight angle with natural head tilt for depth and dimension
pov, point-of-view angle showing the scene as experienced by the subject
professionally shot, expert composition with controlled lighting and precise framing
profile, side view showing the subject's facial silhouette from temple to chin
rack focus, shifting focus from one subject to another within the same frame
rear three-quarter view, angled approximately forty-five degrees between rear and side showing the back at an angle
reference sheet, multiple orthographic views of a character for design documentation
rotated, image or subject turned at an angle from the standard orientation
selfie, self-portrait perspective with the camera held at arm's length
shoulder-level shot, camera positioned at shoulder height for natural conversation framing
split screen, composition divided into distinct panels showing multiple views simultaneously
street level shot, camera at pedestrian street height in an urban environment
studio shot, controlled studio environment with professional lighting and clean background
telephoto shot, compressed perspective with flattened depth from a distant focal length
three sided view, front, side, and back views of the subject arranged together
tilt shift, selective focus creating a miniature diorama effect on real scenes
top-down view, camera aimed straight down from directly above the scene
tracking shot, camera follows the moving subject maintaining consistent framing
two shot angle, composition framing two subjects together in a single shot
ultra wide angle, extremely broad field of view capturing a vast scene with distortion
upper body shot, frames the subject from the waist up including arms and torso
upside-down, subject or entire composition inverted for a surreal disorienting effect
vanishing point, parallel lines converging toward a distant point for strong depth perspective
vignette, gradual darkening along the edges drawing attention toward the center
Waist Shot (WS), frames the subject from the waist up in a standard medium composition
whip pan, rapid horizontal camera movement creating motion blur across the frame
wide angle portrait, portrait shot with a wide lens including surrounding environment
wide angle portrait, portrait shot with a wide lens including surrounding environment, subject positioned with angled stance and relaxed asymmetric posture
wide shot, broad framing showing the full subject and substantial surroundings
zoomed out, camera pulled back to reveal more of the scene and context
